# Allowed signers for verifying release tags in CI (`git verify-tag`).
#
# The release workflow (.github/workflows/release.yml) refuses to build a
# tag that isn't signed by a key listed here.
#
# This is the SAME Secure-Enclave (Secretive) key you sign validibot
# releases with. Your global git config already points at it
# (gpg.format=ssh, tag.gpgsign=true, user.signingkey → the Secretive key),
# so `just release` in this repo signs with the same key — no per-repo
# git config needed.
#
# To rotate or add a signer, append a line of the form:
#   <identity> namespaces="git" <key-type> <base64-public-key> [comment]
# Omit comments that expose a workstation hostname or local account name.
# Print your current public signing key with:
#   cat "$(git config --global user.signingkey)"

